class:: JuniorBCh
summary:: BYOD-derived Pro Junior preamp stage model
categories:: UGens>Filters
related:: Guides/ChowDSPPorts

Description::

JuniorBCh follows BYOD's public `Junior B` processor. The design is hybrid: a neural triode stage model is embedded inside the original wave-digital circuit, and the result can be cascaded from one to four stages with `blend` controlling the dry / processed balance. Mathematically that means the signal is not passing through a single black-box network; it is passing through a structured circuit model whose nonlinear element is itself a learned model.

That hybrid approach matters because it keeps some of the topology and loading behavior of the source circuit while letting the triode element capture richer nonlinear behavior than a simple analytic tube law. The sound sits in the amp-preamp family, with saturation, compression, and transient softening increasing as more stages are engaged.

